  "text": "## CSS Style Change to Layout Paint Chain in Firefox/Gecko\n\nThe complete chain for how CSS style changes trigger layout and paint operations in Firefox:\n\n### 1. Style Change Notification Phase\nWhen CSS properties change (via class/attribute changes, inline style modifications, or stylesheet updates), RestyleManager::PostRestyleEvent (layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp:2383) is called to queue style recalculation. This function posts the element for restyle processing.\n\n### 2. Flush Pending Notifications\nWhen the page needs to be laid out or painted, PresShell::DoFlushPendingNotifications (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:4357) is invoked. This function orchestrates the complete flush sequence by:\n- Calling RestyleManager::ProcessPendingRestyles (layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp:3284)\n- Then calling PresShell::DoFlushLayout (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:10716) which invokes ProcessReflowCommands\n\n### 3. Style Recomputation\nRestyleManager::ProcessPendingRestyles (layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp:3284) delegates to DoProcessPendingRestyles (layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp:3087), which uses the Servo style engine to recompute styles for invalidated elements. This results in updated ComputedStyle objects being attached to elements.\n\n### 4. Frame Style Application\nOnce styles are recomputed, nsIFrame::DidSetComputedStyle (layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp:1240) is called for each affected frame. This hook allows frames to respond to style changes, such as scheduling reflows if the changes affect layout.\n\n### 5. Dirty Frame Marking\nFrames that require layout recomputation call PresShell::FrameNeedsReflow (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:2632). This function:\n- Marks the frame and affected ancestors with dirty state bits\n- Clears intrinsic sizing caches if needed\n- Adds the frame to the dirty roots list (mDirtyRoots)\n- Sets SetNeedLayoutFlush() to schedule reflow processing\n\n### 6. Reflow Processing\nPresShell::ProcessReflowCommands (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:10637) processes all dirty frames:\n- Pops frames from mDirtyRoots using PopShallowestRoot()\n- Calls PresShell::DoReflow (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:10438) for each frame\n- DoReflow creates a ReflowInput and calls frame->Reflow() to recalculate frame geometry\n- After reflow, PresShell::DidDoReflow (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:10365) is called to handle post-reflow tasks\n\n### 7. Paint Scheduling\nDuring DoReflow (line 10463), after the actual reflow, target->SchedulePaint() is called to invalidate the frame for painting. This marks the frame region as needing a paint.\n\n### 8. Display List Building\nWhen painting occurs, PresShell::PaintSynchronously (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:12326) calls PaintAndRequestComposite (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:6421), which delegates to PaintInternal (layout/base/PresShell.cpp:6467).\n\nPaintInternal calls nsLayoutUtils::PaintFrame (layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp:2834), which:\n- Creates or reuses a RetainedDisplayListBuilder (if retained display lists are enabled)\n- Sets up the display list builder with paint parameters\n- Calls builder->BeginFrame() and builder->EnterPresShell()\n- Most importantly, calls aFrame->BuildDisplayListForStackingContext(builder, list) at line 3191 to recursively build the display list from the frame tree\n- Calls builder->LeavePresShell() to finalize\n- Then calls list->PaintRoot() at line 3258\n\n### 9. Display List Painting and WebRender Submission\nnsDisplayList::PaintRoot (layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp:2348) processes the built display list:\n- For WebRender backend (line 2406), it gets the WebRenderLayerManager\n- Calls wrManager->EndTransactionWithoutLayer (layout/layers/wr/WebRenderLayerManager) at line 2464\n- This function sends the display list and associated data to the WebRender backend\n- WebRender then schedules rendering and submits draw commands to the GPU\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n**Style System (layout/style/)**:\n- RestyleManager.cpp: Manages style invalidation and recomputation (PostRestyleEvent, ProcessPendingRestyles, DoProcessPendingRestyles)\n\n**Reflow System (layout/base/)**:\n- PresShell.cpp: Main orchestrator (DoFlushPendingNotifications, FrameNeedsReflow, ProcessReflowCommands, DoReflow, PaintSynchronously, PaintInternal, PaintAndRequestComposite)\n- nsLayoutUtils.cpp: PaintFrame - the bridge between reflow and display list building\n\n**Frame System (layout/generic/)**:\n- nsIFrame.cpp: DidSetComputedStyle hook called when frame styles change\n\n**Display List and Painting (layout/painting/)**:\n- nsDisplayList.cpp: Display list construction and painting (BuildDisplayListForStackingContext called via frame->BuildDisplayListForStackingContext, PaintRoot sends to renderer)\n- nsDisplayList.h: nsDisplayList class definition\n\n**WebRender Integration (gfx/layers/wr/)**:\n- WebRenderLayerManager.cpp/h: EndTransactionWithoutLayer sends the display list to WebRender for rendering\n\nThe complete flow ensures that CSS style changes are efficiently detected, validated changes trigger selective frame reflows, and paint operations are batched into display lists that are submitted to WebRender for GPU-accelerated rendering."
}

